  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Skeletal muscle abnormalities (sarcopenia) and frailty are common complications seen in
      patients with end-stage liver disease. The presence of these complications portends poor
      prognosis. The purpose of this study is to assess the impact of a formal home based video
      strengthening program (REST) on sarcopenia and frailty. We also want to assess the impact of
      this exercise program on complication rates, hospitalization, on quality of life (QOL) and on
      survival.
    </textblock>
